      "id": 1,
      "text": "Bellerose was founded in the early 1900s by Helen Marsh, who wanted to turn former gladiola farmland into a model suburban community.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        1
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Web source 2"
      ],
      "source": "https://www.longislandguide.com/visit/bellerose/"
    },
    {
      "id": 2,
      "text": "Marsh built the village’s first home in 1910 and persuaded the Long Island Rail Road to add a station to serve the new community.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        7
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Web source 2"
      ],
      "source": "https://www.longislandguide.com/visit/bellerose/"
    },
    {
      "id": 3,
      "text": "The village’s civic buildings, including the Village Hall and Fire House, are celebrated for their historical and architectural significance.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        4
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
